node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 16, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'One of of US oldest cities has had only White men as mayors. In November, that changes CNN'.

node.text:
Boston is poised to make history in November with two women of color competing for a mayoral seat that has been occupied by White men for the past 200 years. City Councilors Michelle Wu and Annissa Essaibi George claimed the two top spots in Tuesday’s primary.⁠
⁠
(📸: AP/Getty Images)⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Federal officers will now be banned from using chokeholds and no-knock warrants in the latest nationwide push for more police accountability CNN'.

node.text:
Federal law enforcement officers will be banned from using neck restraints (commonly known as chokeholds) during arrests and using no-knock entries while executing warrants except in rare cases, the Justice Department announced Tuesday. This addresses two aspects of police accountability under federal jurisdiction, but state and local governments have already made these changes over the past two years.⁠
⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 16, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A cave full of ancient paintings sold for $2.2 million. The Osage Nation says it belongs to them CNN'.

node.text:
A cave in Missouri containing 1,000-year-old artwork created by the Osage Nation sold at an auction earlier this week for $2.2 million dollars. For the Osage Nation, whose ancestors created much of the artwork in the cave, the sale came as a huge blow.⁠
⁠
“It is our ancestors who are buried there in that cave,” Andrea Hunter, tribal historic preservation officer for the Osage Nation, told CNN. “It is our ancestors that created the images that are on the walls and conducted the rituals that took place. It is absolutely the most sacred site that we have. And it rightfully should be in our ownership.”⁠
⁠
(📸: Alan Cressler/AP)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Drag queen RuPaul has a new namesake and it's a fabulous, rainbow-colored fly'.

node.text:
Australian entomologists named a fly species after RuPaul — the titan of drag queens. The soldier fly, whose Latin name is Opaluma rupaul, is characterized by its iridescent colors.⁠
⁠
"I'd been watching a lot of 'RuPaul's Drag Race' when I was examining the specimen under the microscope, so it was on my mind!" entomologist Dr. Bryan Lessard, also known as "Bry the Fly Guy," told CNN.⁠
⁠
(📸: BBC/RuPaul's Drag Race UK/Bryan Lessard/CSIRO)

node.text: Around 3,000 health care workers have been suspended in France after failing to meet a government requirement to get vaccinated against Covid-19, French Health Minister Olivier Véran told French radio station RTL Thursday. A dozen resignations have been handed in by health care workers over the policy, Veran said.

node.text:
Millions are under flash flood watches Thursday as Post-Tropical Cyclone Nicholas lingers over the central Gulf Coast, threatening to dump even more rain. The storm is expected to move north slowly in the upcoming days, the Weather Prediction Center said.⁠
⁠
(📸: Victor Castellon)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 16, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says '1,400 dolphins were killed in the Faroe Islands in one day The marine conservation group Sea Shepherd called the killings a 'brutal and badly mishandled' massacre CNN'.

node.text:
More than 1,400 white-sided dolphins were killed Sunday night in the Faroe Islands in what local authorities said was a traditional whaling hunt. The annual whale hunt has long been criticized by animal rights groups, but locals have defended the practice.⁠
⁠
(📸: Sea Shepherd/AP)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 16, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Rare photos show the early years of NASA's space shuttle era UniterCh.i Ih CNN'.

node.text: 🚀 450 rare photos have been released in a new book showing the early years of NASA's space shuttle era, offering a unique view into the early development of the shuttle. “One of our trademarks is to concentrate on unusual, rarely seen or unpublished images," John Bisney, the co-author of the book, said. "If you go to the library and pull a book on the shuttle off the shelf, you typically see the same few hundred pictures in every book. And that's understandable, because they are great pictures. But there's a lot more to show you." (📸: NASA)

node.text:
History has been made as a SpaceX rocket soared into orbit Wednesday evening, carrying four people — none of whom are professional astronauts. The launch of Inspiration4 from NASA's Kennedy Space Center kicks off the first-ever mission to Earth's orbit crewed entirely by tourists.

(📸: SpaceX and John Kraus/Inspiration4)
